Start
/ Builder smoke test — exercises the four primitives that cover ~90% of the
/ builder's hard surface: set variable, condition.if, loop.foreach, goal.call.
/ Run via `plang '--build={"files":["BuilderSanity/BuilderSanity.test.goal","BuilderSanity/AddItem.goal","BuilderSanity/MarkBig.goal","BuilderSanity/Finalize.goal"],"cache":false}'`
/ from the Tests/ directory before trusting `plang --test` results.
- set %total% = 0
- set %items% = [1, 2, 3]
- foreach %items%, call AddItem item=%item%
- if %total% is greater than 5, call MarkBig
- call Finalize
- assert %total% equals 6
- assert %label% equals 'big-and-done'
